{{Use Australian English|date=May 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox waterfall | name = Herbert River Falls | photo = | photo_width = 250px | photo_caption = | map = Queensland | relief = yes | map_width = 250px | coordinates = {{coord|18|14|06|S|145|22|15|E|type:waterbody_region:AU-QLD_scale:50000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref>{{Gazetteer of Australia|name=Herbert River Falls|feature=QLD15763}}</ref><ref name=dnrm>{{cite QPN|15763|Herbert River Falls|accessdate=13 September 2015}}</ref> | location = [[Far North Queensland|Far North]] [[Queensland]], [[Australia]] | type = [[Waterfall#Types|Plunge]] | elevation = {{convert|505|m}}<ref name=bonzle>{{cite web|url=http://www.bonzle.com/c/a?a=p&p=253372&cmd=sp|title=Map of Herbert River Falls, QLD|work=Bonzle Digital Atlas of Australia|accessdate=23 May 2014|date=}}</ref> | height = {{convert|56|-|75|m}}<ref name=bonzle/> | height_longest = | number_drops = | width = | average_width = | watercourse = [[Herbert River]] | average_flow = | world_rank = }} The '''Herbert River Falls''' is a [[Waterfall#Types|plunge waterfall]] on the [[Herbert River]] that is located in the [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage Area|World Heritage]]{{endash}}listed [[Wet Tropics World Heritage Area|Wet Tropics]] in the [[Far North Queensland|Far North]] region of [[Queensland]], [[Australia]].
==Location and features== The falls are located on the northern boundary of the [[Girringun National Park]], west of {{QLDcity|Cardwell}}, in the [[Cassowary Coast Region|Cassowary Coast]] [[Local government in Australia|local government area]], approximately {{convert|162|km}} northwest of the river's [[mouth (river)|mouth]] at {{QLDcity|Ingham}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/cgi-bin/ahdb/search.pl?mode=place_detail;place_id=8996|title=Herbert River Falls Gorge and Rainforest Plateau, Abergowrie-Ingham Rd, Abergowrie, QLD, Australia|work=[[Australian Heritage Database]]|publisher=[[Department of the Environment (Australia)|Department of the Environment]], [[Government of Australia|Australian Government]]|date=26 April 1988|accessdate=23 May 2014}}</ref> The waterfall plunges from the [[Atherton Tableland]] at an elevation of {{convert|505|m}}<ref name=bonzle/> and falls between {{convert|56|-|75|m}}<ref name=bonzle/> into the Herbert River Gorge below.
