The following is a [[:Category:City timelines|timeline]] of the history of the [[List of cities in Burkina Faso|city]] of [[Ouagadougou]], [[Burkina Faso]].
{{Dynamic list}}
{{TOC right}}

==Prior to 20th century==
* 1896 - 5 September: Ouagadougou taken by French forces; city burned.{{sfn|Johnson|2010}}

==20th century==
[[File:COLLECTIE TROPENMUSEUM Een man op de fiets in de straten van Ouagadougou achter hem marktwaar dat hangend aan fietsen is uitgestald TMnr 20010507.jpg|thumb|right|View of Ouagadougou, 1970s]]
{{History of Burkina Faso}}

* 1904 - Population: 4,000 (estimate).{{sfn|Johnson|2010}}
* 1919 - Ouagadougou designated capital of French colonial [[French Upper Volta|Upper Volta]].{{sfn|Johnson|2010}}
* 1920 - Population: 19,332.<ref name=Statesman1921>{{cite book |title=[[Statesman's Year-Book]] |year=1921 |location=London |publisher= Macmillan and Co.|chapter= France: Africa: French West Africa and the Sahara: Colony of the Upper Volta |chapterurl= https://archive.org/stream/statesmansyearbo1921londuoft#page/901/mode/1up |via=[[Internet Archive]] |pages= 895–903 |quote= Ouaga-dougou }}</ref>
* 1921 - Catholic [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Ouagadougou|Apostolic Vicariate of Ouagadougou]] established.<ref>{{cite web |title=Chronology of Catholic Dioceses: Burkina Faso |url= http://www.katolsk.no/organisasjon/verden/chronology/burkina |publisher=[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Oslo]] |location=Norway |accessdate= 10 July 2017 }}</ref>
* 1932 - Upper Volta becomes part of Côte d'Ivoire; capital moves from Ouagadougou.{{sfn|Johnson|2010}}
* 1936 - [[Ouagadougou Cathedral]] built.
* 1955
** [[Abidjan]]-Ouagadougou railway begins operating.{{sfn|Johnson|2010}}
** [[Étoile Filante de Ouagadougou]] (football club) formed.
* 1956 - [[Joseph Ouédraogo]] becomes mayor.
* 1960 - City becomes capital of independent Burkina Faso.{{sfn|Johnson|2010}}
* 1961
** Population: 59,126.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1960_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1965 |year=1966 |publisher=[[Statistical Office of the United Nations]] |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=140–161 |quote=Upper Volta }}</ref>
** [[Joseph Conombo]] becomes mayor.
* 1966 - Population: 77,500 (estimate).<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1970_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1975 |year=1976 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=253–279 |quote=Upper Volta }}</ref>
* 1969 - [[Panafrican Film and Television Festival of Ouagadougou]] begins.<ref name=MMA-afu11>{{cite web |url= http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/ht/11/afu.html |title= Western and Central Sudan, 1900 A.D.–present: Key Events |work= Heilbrunn Timeline of Art History |publisher=[[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] |location=New York |accessdate= 14 July 2017 }}</ref>
* 1972 - [[Koupéla]]-Ouagadougou [[Trans-Sahelian Highway|road]] built.<ref name=AFDB2003 />
* 1974 - [[University of Ouagadougou]] founded.
* 1977 - [[Santos FC (Burkina Faso)|Santos FC]] (football club) formed.
* 1982 - [[Boromo]]-Ouagadougou [[Trans-Sahelian Highway|road]] built.<ref name=AFDB2003>{{citation |author1=[[Sweco]] |author2= Nordic Consulting Group |url=http://www.afdb.org/fileadmin/uploads/afdb/Documents/Project-and-Operations/00473227-EN-TAH-FINAL-VOL2.PDF |publisher=[[African Development Bank]] and [[United Nations Economic Commission for Africa]] |title=Review of the Implementation Status of the Trans African Highways and the Missing Links |volume= 2: Description of Corridors |year=2003 }}</ref>
* 1983 - Population: 307,937 (estimate).<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1980_round.htm |title=1985 Demographic Yearbook |year=1987 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=247–289 }}</ref>
* 1984 - [[Stade du 4 Août]] (stadium) opens.
* 1986 - [[Bobo-Dioulasso]]-Ouagadougou [[Trans-Sahelian Highway|road]] built.<ref name=AFDB2003 />
* 1990 - [[AS SONABEL]] (football club) formed.
* 1991
** ''[[Le Pays (Burkina Faso)|Le Pays]]'' newspaper begins publication.
** Population: 634,479 (estimate).<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1990_round.htm |title=1995 Demographic Yearbook |year=1997 |author=United Nations Department for Economic and Social Information and Policy Analysis, Statistics Division |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=262–321 }}</ref>
* 1995 - [[Simon Compaoré]] becomes mayor.
* 1996
** [[Radio Salankoloto]] begins broadcasting.<ref name=Europa2004>{{cite book |title=Africa South of the Sahara 2004 |series=Regional Surveys of the World |publisher= [[Europa Publications]] |year=2004 |isbn= 1857431839 |chapter= Burkina Faso: Directory |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jj4J-AXGDaQC }}</ref>
** Population: 709,736.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/dyb2004.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 2004 |year= |publisher=[[United Nations Statistics Division]] |title= Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 or more inhabitants }}</ref>
* 1998 - 28 February: [[1998 African Cup of Nations Final]] football contest played in Ouagadougou.

==21st century==
[[File:Ouaga aerial view.jpg|thumb|right|Aerial view of Ouagadougou, 2007]]

* 2004
** November: Meeting of the [[Organisation internationale de la Francophonie]] held in city.
** Meeting of the [[Association Internationale des Maires Francophones]] held in city.
* 2006 - Population: 1,475,223.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/dyb2015.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 2015 |year=2016 |publisher=United Nations Statistics Division |title= Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 or more inhabitants }}</ref>
* 2007
** August: [[2007 African Junior Athletics Championships]] held in city.
** United States military [[List of United States drone bases|drone base]] established at [[Ouagadougou Airport|airport]].
* 2014 - October–November: [[2014 Burkinabé uprising]].
* 2016
** 15 January: [[2016 Ouagadougou attacks]] by militant Islamists occur.<ref name=bbc>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-13072857 |accessdate= 10 July 2017 |title= Burkina Faso Profile: Timeline |work= [[BBC News]] }}</ref>
** Armand Béouindé becomes mayor.<ref>{{citation |url=http://lepays.bf/mairie-centrale-de-ouagadougou-armand-beouinde-installe-fonctions/ |language=fr |work= Le Pays |location= Ouagadougou |title=Mairie centrale de Ouagadougou: Armand Béouindé installé dans ses fonctions |date= 1 July 2016 }}</ref>
* 2017 - 13 August: [[2017 Ouagadougou attack]].

